arChildNodes.szComment:
The PLAYER pulls the book from the goo and quickly flips through. It is full of notes and drawings about the vault, our version of the grail diary. 
We hear faint chanting in the distance.

ERU is gesturing ahead. The camera follows his gesture, pushing through a swarm of tendrils to eventually land on the source of the Horadric chanting: NEYRELLE. 

pronunciation: ah-kah-raht cheers cha cham, 
milly doom bith ee-chith, 
milly lil em bith thoo-sood, 
thoo coo-doe marth sole ahn
She kneels upon a rock. She looks run-down, haggard. She holds the soulstone in her hand, arm trembling.

Her eyes shoot open to meet the Player’s. She’s startled to see them here, and her face floods with emotion. 
There is sadness and relief and just the hint of tears as her voice cracks painfully.
As the Player starts to approach her, we see a little more. Black ichor covers her, and her veins show on her outstretched hand. Her eyes are bloodshot. 
She shakes her head no and glances to the side. There, in the murky darkness, we hear Mephisto’s whispers get louder and two eyes peer out. 
For a second, the Player freezes, their gaze locked. We hear Mephisto’s voice before we see him.

He jerks his head and Neyrelle seizes in pain. The ground rumbles, rocks lifting as if the land around her was having a seizure.
Hollows erupt out of the ground around the area, between the player and Neyrelle. Wolphisto retreats into darkness.

// But Neyrelle doesn’t take it without a fight. She pushes back against him ferociously.
He cringes, surprisingly hurt by the effort. His connection with Neyrelle runs both ways.
